Japan Stocks Jump as Progress Seen on Crisis at Stricken Nuclear Reactor

-- B y   N i c k   G e n t l e
-- 
2011-03-22T00:16:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/japan-stocks-jump-as-progress-seen-on-crisis-at-stricken-nuclear-reactor.html
Japanese stocks surged, with the
Nikkei 225 Stock Average and the Topix index both jumping more
than 3.5 percent, as the country made progress stabilizing
nuclear reactors 11 days after its worst ever earthquake.  The Nikkei 225 advanced 3.9 percent to 9,561.22 at 9:13
a.m. in  Tokyo , while the broader Topix index climbed 3.8 percent
to 862.31.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nick Gentle at 
 ngentle2@bloomberg.net  